body:
In my case --protect_lib output contains:
    localparam int protectlib_hash__V = 4287673301;

Which yields the following on compilation:
Warning-[DCTL] Decimal constant too large
/usr/julien/fias_core/tb/verilator/obj/verilated_riscv_cpu.sv, 337
  Decimal constant '4287673301' is too large as a 32bit signed constant, it 
  should be smaller than 2147483648.
  VCS is using converted signed value '-7293995' instead.
  To make it an unsigned constant, please use sized constant format.

The following patch resolves the issue:
```cpp
--- a/src/V3ProtectLib.cpp
+++ b/src/V3ProtectLib.cpp
@@ -197,7 +197,7 @@ private:
         // CPP hash value
         addComment(txtp, fl, "Hash value to make sure this file and the corresponding");
         addComment(txtp, fl, "library agree");
-        m_hashValuep = new AstTextBlock(fl, "localparam int protectlib_hash__V = ");
+        m_hashValuep = new AstTextBlock(fl, "localparam int protectlib_hash__V = 32'd");
         txtp->addNodep(m_hashValuep);
         txtp->addText(fl, "\n");
```
